00:44:55.969 --> 00:44:59.969
This is what Jesus said at Luke chapter 5 verse 31.

00:44:59.969 --> 00:45:03.969
Those who are healthy do not need a physician,

00:45:03.969 --> 00:45:06.969
but those who are ill do.

00:45:06.969 --> 00:45:09.969
Now, of course, that decision is up to you,

00:45:09.969 --> 00:45:11.969
but it's there in the Scripture.

00:45:11.969 --> 00:45:13.969
It may be that you need

00:45:13.969 --> 00:45:16.969
the help of a physician, someone who's qualified

00:45:16.969 --> 00:45:20.969
to look into certain matters.

00:45:20.969 --> 00:45:24.969
Please rejoice in knowing that you have Jehovah's approval.

00:45:24.969 --> 00:45:28.969
Don't doubt it, not even for a moment.

00:45:28.969 --> 00:45:33.969
Now granted, it's not easy to deal with mental

00:45:33.969 --> 00:45:36.969
or emotional distress.

00:45:36.969 --> 00:45:41.969
But keep in mind that Jehovah understands

00:45:41.969 --> 00:45:46.969
and he will help you to keep on enduring.

00:45:46.969 --> 00:45:50.969
And your loyal endurance brings your Jehovah's approval,

00:45:50.969 --> 00:45:55.969
which is one of the greatest reasons that we have for rejoicing.

00:45:55.969 --> 00:45:59.969
Know that God has not left you.

00:45:59.969 --> 00:46:06.969
You have His approval like a large shield surrounding you

00:46:06.969 --> 00:46:08.969
and His blessing.

00:46:08.969 --> 00:46:12.969
And rejoice in that knowledge and keep on rejoicing

00:46:12.969 --> 00:46:18.300
despite distress.

00:46:18.300 --> 00:46:21.300
Brother Garrett Loesch, a member of the governing body

00:46:21.300 --> 00:46:25.300
will now present the next talk of this symposium.

00:46:25.300 --> 00:46:36.699
We can rejoice despite persecution.

00:46:36.699 --> 00:46:38.699
Since the beginning of Christianity,

00:46:38.699 --> 00:46:41.699
Christians have been persecuted.

00:46:41.699 --> 00:46:46.699
Please locate with me 2 Corinthians chapter 11.

00:46:46.699 --> 00:46:51.699
Paul experienced the persecution and referred to it

00:46:51.699 --> 00:46:58.699
in 2 Corinthians chapter 11 verses 23 to 25.

00:46:58.699 --> 00:47:02.699
And it says, are they ministers of Christ?

00:47:02.699 --> 00:47:06.699
I reply like a madman, I am more outstandingly one.

00:47:06.699 --> 00:47:10.699
I've done more work, been imprisoned more often,

00:47:10.699 --> 00:47:15.699
suffered countless beatings and experienced many near deaths.

00:47:15.699 --> 00:47:20.699
Five times I received 40 strokes, less one from the Jews.

00:47:20.699 --> 00:47:23.699
Three times I was beaten with rods.

00:47:23.699 --> 00:47:26.699
Once I was stoned, three times I experienced shipwreck.

00:47:26.699 --> 00:47:32.460
A night in the day I've spent in the open sea.

00:47:32.460 --> 00:47:36.460
Shortly after recounting His many difficulties,

00:47:36.460 --> 00:47:41.460
in chapter 12 verse 10, Paul wrote,

00:47:41.460 --> 00:47:46.460
so I take pleasure in weaknesses, in insults,

00:47:46.460 --> 00:47:49.460
in times of need, in persecutions,

00:47:49.460 --> 00:47:51.460
and difficult is for Christ.

00:47:51.460 --> 00:47:54.460
For when I'm weak, I am powerful.

00:47:54.460 --> 00:48:00.780
Of course, Paul took no pleasure in persecution itself.

00:48:00.780 --> 00:48:04.780
But he rejoiced because of what can result from it,

00:48:04.780 --> 00:48:08.780
contributing to Jehovah's vindication.

00:48:08.780 --> 00:48:16.780
Find the Philippians chapter 114 and then verse 18.

00:48:16.780 --> 00:48:22.780
Persecution gives us also an opportunity to see Jehovah act

00:48:22.780 --> 00:48:26.780
in behalf of His people and magnify His name.

00:48:26.780 --> 00:48:29.780
It can lead to a fine witness.

00:48:29.780 --> 00:48:35.780
In Philippians 1 verse 14 and 18, Paul wrote,

00:48:35.780 --> 00:48:42.559
Now most of the brothers in the Lord have gained confidence

00:48:42.559 --> 00:48:44.559
because of my prison bonds,

00:48:44.559 --> 00:48:47.559
and they are showing all the more courage

00:48:47.559 --> 00:48:52.559
to speak the word of God fearlessly.

00:48:52.559 --> 00:48:55.559
And verse 18, with what result?

00:48:55.559 --> 00:48:59.559
Only that in every way, whether in pretense or in truth,

00:48:59.559 --> 00:49:03.559
Christ is being proclaimed and I rejoice over this.

00:49:03.559 --> 00:49:09.000
In fact, I will also keep on rejoicing.

00:49:09.000 --> 00:49:13.000
Instead of weakening our relationship with Jehovah and our hope,

00:49:13.000 --> 00:49:18.000
persecution can strengthen it.

00:49:18.000 --> 00:49:23.000
In the discussion recorded at Romans chapter 5, 3 and 4,

00:49:23.000 --> 00:49:25.000
Paul explains,

00:49:25.000 --> 00:49:28.000
Let us exalt while in tribulations.

00:49:28.000 --> 00:49:32.000
Endurance leads to an approved condition,

00:49:32.000 --> 00:49:36.000
the approved condition in turn to hope,

00:49:36.000 --> 00:49:40.000
and hope does not lead to disappointment.

00:49:40.000 --> 00:49:47.000
There is no doubt that hope helps us mightily to endure persecution.

00:49:47.000 --> 00:49:51.000
The Bible uses the word hope in different contexts.

00:49:51.000 --> 00:49:54.000
It speaks of the hope of salvation,

00:49:54.000 --> 00:49:58.000
which can refer to spiritual salvation.

00:49:58.000 --> 00:50:02.000
There is hope of surviving Armageddon.

00:50:02.000 --> 00:50:07.000
There is hope of everlasting life on the Paradise Earth.

00:50:07.000 --> 00:50:11.000
There is hope of immortality in heaven.

00:50:11.000 --> 00:50:17.000
What hope was he talking about in Romans chapter 5, 3 and 4,

00:50:17.000 --> 00:50:20.000
about the heavenly hope?

00:50:20.000 --> 00:50:22.000
Look at the context.

00:50:22.000 --> 00:50:27.000
Romans 5, 2, and the second part of the verse says,

00:50:27.000 --> 00:50:34.000
Let us rejoice based on the hope of the glory of God.

00:50:34.000 --> 00:50:38.000
All Christians in the first century had the heavenly hope.

00:50:38.000 --> 00:50:43.000
Their hope was not just that problems or well conditions would be resolved

00:50:43.000 --> 00:50:46.000
or that they would get healed from some sickness.

00:50:46.000 --> 00:50:49.000
Their hope was the heavenly hope.

00:50:49.000 --> 00:50:52.000
Colossians 1, 3 says,

00:50:52.000 --> 00:50:56.000
We always thank God when we pray for you,

00:50:56.000 --> 00:51:03.000
because of the hope that is being reserved for you in the heavens.

00:51:03.000 --> 00:51:10.000
Now, please turn to Romans chapter 8, verse 20 and 21.

00:51:10.000 --> 00:51:17.000
The great crowd of Jehovah's witnesses today hope that Jehovah will reward them

00:51:17.000 --> 00:51:20.000
in an earthly paradise.

00:51:20.000 --> 00:51:30.000
Paul pointed to that hope when he wrote in Romans chapter 8, verse 20 and 21.

00:51:30.000 --> 00:51:35.000
For the creation was subjected to futility, not by its own will,

00:51:35.000 --> 00:51:40.000
but through the one who subjected it on the basis of hope,

00:51:40.000 --> 00:51:48.000
that the creation itself will be also set free from enslavement to corruption

00:51:48.000 --> 00:51:52.000
and have the glorious freedom of the children of God.

00:51:52.000 --> 00:51:59.440
However, when Paul said in Romans chapter 12, verse 12,

00:51:59.440 --> 00:52:01.440
rejoice in the hope ahead.

00:52:01.440 --> 00:52:04.440
He meant the heavenly hope.

00:52:04.440 --> 00:52:10.440
But the other sheep also can rejoice in the hope that is ahead of them.

00:52:10.440 --> 00:52:14.440
So then we can all rejoice triumphantly.

00:52:14.440 --> 00:52:17.440
The world's hope is dark.

00:52:17.440 --> 00:52:19.440
Your hope is bright.

00:52:19.440 --> 00:52:21.440
The world's hope is collapsing.

00:52:21.440 --> 00:52:24.440
Your hope nears fulfillment.

00:52:24.440 --> 00:52:27.440
The world's hope is based on credulity.

00:52:27.440 --> 00:52:30.440
Your hope is based on faith.

00:52:30.440 --> 00:52:33.440
The world's hope leads to disappointment.

00:52:33.440 --> 00:52:36.440
Your hope leads to success.

00:52:36.440 --> 00:52:39.440
For with the new world, so very near,

00:52:39.440 --> 00:52:42.440
our fondest hopes whether heavenly or earthly

00:52:42.440 --> 00:52:47.440
will soon be realized to our eternal satisfaction.

00:52:47.440 --> 00:52:53.440
Let's read together Titus chapter 2, verse 13,

00:52:53.440 --> 00:53:03.800
while we wait for the happy hope

00:53:03.800 --> 00:53:07.800
and glorious manifestation of the great God

00:53:07.800 --> 00:53:10.800
and of our Savior Jesus Christ.

00:53:10.800 --> 00:53:17.079
Furthermore, according to Romans 8, 24 and 25,

00:53:17.079 --> 00:53:21.079
hope will help us to endure.

00:53:21.079 --> 00:53:25.079
Hope that is seen is not hope.

00:53:25.079 --> 00:53:28.079
But if we hope for what we do not see,

00:53:28.079 --> 00:53:33.079
we keep on waiting for it with endurance, the Scripture says.

00:53:33.079 --> 00:53:36.079
There are degrees of hope.

00:53:36.079 --> 00:53:41.079
How can we strengthen or deepen our hope?

00:53:41.079 --> 00:53:44.079
As to the term hope in the Bible,

00:53:44.079 --> 00:53:46.079
the basic sense of the Greek term,

00:53:46.079 --> 00:53:52.079
alpes, used here, means expectation of good.

00:53:52.079 --> 00:53:57.079
In this context, Paul mentions hope last in the series,

00:53:57.079 --> 00:54:02.079
after tribulation, endurance, and approved condition.

00:54:02.079 --> 00:54:06.079
So he is obviously not referring to the initial hope

00:54:06.079 --> 00:54:09.079
gained by accepting the good news from God.

00:54:09.079 --> 00:54:13.079
Rather, he is referring to a reinforced hope

00:54:13.079 --> 00:54:17.079
that a Christian can gain after enduring.

00:54:17.079 --> 00:54:20.079
When a Christian faithfully endures trials,

00:54:20.079 --> 00:54:24.079
he realizes that he has God's approval.

00:54:24.079 --> 00:54:30.460
This realization strengthens his initial hope.

00:54:30.460 --> 00:54:36.460
Like Paul, we can rejoice despite persecution.

00:54:36.460 --> 00:54:41.460
We may encounter hateful words and actions at school,

00:54:41.460 --> 00:54:43.460
at work in our family,

00:54:43.460 --> 00:54:47.460
or as a result of governmental restrictions.

00:54:47.460 --> 00:54:52.460
In Matthew chapter 5, 11 and 12,

00:54:52.460 --> 00:54:56.460
in the sermon on the Mount,

00:54:56.460 --> 00:54:59.460
Jesus said the following.

00:54:59.460 --> 00:55:06.119
Happy are you when people reproach you and persecute you,

00:55:06.119 --> 00:55:11.119
and lyingly say every sort of wicked things against you for my sake.

00:55:11.119 --> 00:55:17.119
Rejoice and be overjoyed since your reward is great in the heavens,

00:55:17.119 --> 00:55:21.119
for in that way they persecuted the prophets prior to you.

00:55:21.119 --> 00:55:28.010
As you watch the following video, note which provisions

00:55:28.010 --> 00:55:43.139
helped our brother and sister to rejoice despite persecution.

00:55:43.139 --> 00:55:53.289
Early one morning, armed Russian special forces broke into my home.

00:55:53.289 --> 00:55:58.289
They handcuffed me and searched my place.

00:55:58.289 --> 00:56:01.289
They took me to the FSB office for interrogation.

00:56:01.289 --> 00:56:09.260
Two days later, the court sentenced me to pre-trial detention.

00:56:09.260 --> 00:56:13.260
I was scared because I didn't know how I would be treated in prison.

00:56:13.260 --> 00:56:16.260
Threatening that things would get worse for me,

00:56:16.260 --> 00:56:20.260
the officer demanded that I incriminate myself, admit guilt,

00:56:20.260 --> 00:56:23.260
and give the names of my fellow believers.

00:56:23.260 --> 00:56:26.260
I also really missed my dear wife.

00:56:26.260 --> 00:56:28.260
It was so hard without her.

00:56:28.260 --> 00:56:33.260
For two months, I didn't have any spiritual food or a Bible.

00:56:33.260 --> 00:56:36.260
So I decided to make one.

00:56:36.260 --> 00:56:40.260
My wife sent me a notebook, and every day I wrote down verses

00:56:40.260 --> 00:56:42.260
that I was able to remember.

00:56:42.260 --> 00:56:47.260
After I had written about 500 verses, I was given a Bible.

00:56:47.260 --> 00:56:52.260
Because I was so spiritually hungry, I read it through in four months.

00:56:52.260 --> 00:56:55.260
During this time, I wrote letters to my wife and friends

00:56:55.260 --> 00:56:59.260
and shared interesting things that I learned from my reading.

00:56:59.260 --> 00:57:03.260
But the letters I received from my friends and my dear wife

00:57:03.260 --> 00:57:07.260
gave me the feeling that the brothers and sisters were so close to me,

00:57:07.260 --> 00:57:10.260
as if they were in the cells next to me.

00:57:10.260 --> 00:57:16.739
I wasn't lonely. I felt as if my friends were right there with me.

00:57:16.739 --> 00:57:20.739
Pre-trial detention isolates a person from society,

00:57:20.739 --> 00:57:24.739
but it's impossible to isolate someone from Jehovah.

00:57:24.739 --> 00:57:27.739
Throughout the day, I prayed to Jehovah many times,

00:57:27.739 --> 00:57:29.739
but I especially waited for bad time.

00:57:29.739 --> 00:57:33.739
When everyone wasn't bad and only the nightlight was on,

00:57:33.739 --> 00:57:36.739
I could talk to Jehovah as much as I wanted.

00:57:36.739 --> 00:57:40.739
There were times when I was all alone in the cell.

00:57:40.739 --> 00:57:43.739
And of course, I took advantage of the situation.

00:57:43.739 --> 00:57:50.739
I would get down on my knees and would literally cry as I prayed to Jehovah.

00:57:50.739 --> 00:57:54.739
I decided to write my requests to God on a sheet of paper

00:57:54.739 --> 00:57:57.739
and then mark off the ones that he answered.

00:57:57.739 --> 00:58:01.739
I was convinced that Jehovah was very close to me.

00:58:01.739 --> 00:58:05.739
I also quietly sang our songs throughout the day.

00:58:05.739 --> 00:58:09.739
But when I was all alone, I sang at the top of my voice.

00:58:10.739 --> 00:58:13.739
I also tried to give a witness whenever possible.

00:58:13.739 --> 00:58:15.739
We discussed a variety of topics,

00:58:15.739 --> 00:58:19.739
everything from tattoos to the King of the North.

00:58:19.739 --> 00:58:23.739
All my fears and anxieties were for nothing.

00:58:23.739 --> 00:58:26.739
I was in detention 343 days,

00:58:26.739 --> 00:58:30.739
and not even a hair fell from my head.

00:58:30.739 --> 00:58:33.739
This was the most interesting year of my life,

00:58:33.739 --> 00:58:37.739
an excellent school to help refine my spiritual qualities.

00:58:37.739 --> 00:58:40.739
I have never felt so close to Jehovah.

00:58:40.739 --> 00:58:44.739
What a great honor to uphold God's sovereignty in this way.

00:58:44.739 --> 00:58:53.980
What is helping you today to rejoice

00:58:53.980 --> 00:58:57.980
despite any opposition you may be experiencing now?

00:58:57.980 --> 00:59:00.980
It is your relationship with Jehovah,

00:59:00.980 --> 00:59:04.980
the brotherhood, your heavenly or earthly hope,

00:59:04.980 --> 00:59:06.980
all these things.

00:59:06.980 --> 00:59:14.800
Maybe rejoice in the love of Jehovah and our brothers.

00:59:14.800 --> 00:59:17.800
If you are enduring persecution,

00:59:17.800 --> 00:59:19.800
be assured that your brothers,

00:59:19.800 --> 00:59:21.800
not only your friends,

00:59:21.800 --> 00:59:23.800
not only brothers in your congregation,

00:59:23.800 --> 00:59:27.800
but all around the earth are praying in your behalf.

00:59:27.800 --> 00:59:32.800
Angels observe you and feel proud if you stay faithful.

00:59:32.800 --> 00:59:36.800
You can greatly contribute to the encouragement

00:59:36.800 --> 00:59:39.800
of the faithful angels.

00:59:39.800 --> 00:59:43.800
Like Jehovah, Jesus, and the angels,

00:59:43.800 --> 00:59:46.800
your brothers can take pride in you

00:59:46.800 --> 00:59:49.800
and rejoice because of your endurance

00:59:49.800 --> 00:59:55.719
and faith despite persecution.

00:59:55.719 --> 00:59:57.719
Brother William Turner and Helper

00:59:57.719 --> 01:00:00.719
to the Service Committee will now present

01:00:00.719 --> 01:00:02.719
the next talk of this symposium

01:00:02.719 --> 01:00:05.719
we can rejoice despite hunger.

01:00:05.719 --> 01:00:15.150
How do you feel when you miss a meal

01:00:15.150 --> 01:00:18.150
or haven't eaten for some time?

01:00:18.150 --> 01:00:21.150
You know, for many, it affects their mood,

01:00:21.150 --> 01:00:24.150
their ability to concentrate,

01:00:24.150 --> 01:00:28.150
sometimes their ability to even think straight.

01:00:28.150 --> 01:00:32.150
But what if that hunger was beyond our control?

01:00:32.150 --> 01:00:35.150
Or prolonged to the point where we had no other choice

01:00:35.150 --> 01:00:37.150
but to be hungry?

01:00:37.150 --> 01:00:41.150
Well, that was the situation the Apostle Paul found himself in

01:00:41.150 --> 01:00:44.150
as he engaged in his ministry.

01:00:44.150 --> 01:00:47.150
For example, a second Corinthians 1127,

01:00:47.150 --> 01:00:50.150
Paul said that he was in hunger and thirst

01:00:50.150 --> 01:00:53.150
and frequently without food.

01:00:53.150 --> 01:00:55.150
This likely occurred while Paul was traveling

01:00:55.150 --> 01:00:59.150
through desolate regions or hot desert areas.

01:00:59.150 --> 01:01:01.150
At times, he may have been hungry and thirsty

01:01:01.150 --> 01:01:04.150
because of being dependent on strangers

01:01:04.150 --> 01:01:06.150
or on whatever provisions he could obtain

01:01:06.150 --> 01:01:10.150
through his own labors in unfamiliar surroundings.

01:01:10.150 --> 01:01:14.150
Paul also lived during the time of a great famine,

01:01:14.150 --> 01:01:16.150
a famine which lasted more than three years

01:01:16.150 --> 01:01:19.150
and caused oppressive poverty in Judea

01:01:19.150 --> 01:01:22.150
and Jerusalem.

01:01:22.150 --> 01:01:26.150
But despite facing all these times without food,

01:01:26.150 --> 01:01:31.150
it's interesting to note the attitude of the Apostle Paul.

01:01:31.150 --> 01:01:33.150
A second Corinthians chapter 6 verse 10,

01:01:33.150 --> 01:01:36.150
he describes himself in his fellow Christians

01:01:36.150 --> 01:01:43.150
as sorrowing but ever rejoicing.

01:01:43.150 --> 01:01:45.150
So Paul acknowledged that difficult times

01:01:45.150 --> 01:01:49.150
could bring a measure of sorrow and distress.

01:01:49.150 --> 01:01:53.150
But how was he able to rejoice?

01:01:53.150 --> 01:01:59.150
To have this inner joy despite his hunger?

01:01:59.150 --> 01:02:00.150
Well, notice his answer.

01:02:00.150 --> 01:02:04.150
Turn with me in your Bible's please to the book of Philippians.

01:02:04.150 --> 01:02:11.150
And we're going to read Philippians chapter 4 verses 11 through 13.

01:02:11.150 --> 01:02:18.389
Paul says, not that I am saying this because I am in need,

01:02:18.389 --> 01:02:20.389
but I have learned to be self-sufficient

01:02:20.389 --> 01:02:22.389
regardless of my circumstances.

01:02:22.389 --> 01:02:25.389
I know how to be low on provisions

01:02:25.389 --> 01:02:27.389
and how to have an abundance.

01:02:27.389 --> 01:02:31.389
In everything and in all circumstances,

01:02:31.389 --> 01:02:34.389
I have learned the secret of both how to be full

01:02:34.389 --> 01:02:37.389
and how to hunger, both how to have an abundance

01:02:37.389 --> 01:02:40.389
and how to do without.

01:02:40.389 --> 01:02:45.389
For all things I have the strength through the one who gives me power.

01:02:45.389 --> 01:02:49.829
Did you note in verse 12,

01:02:49.829 --> 01:02:54.829
Paul speaks of learning the secret of both how to be full

01:02:54.829 --> 01:02:56.829
and how to hunger.

01:02:56.829 --> 01:03:02.829
This secret involves relying on Jehovah for life's necessities

01:03:02.829 --> 01:03:06.829
and being satisfied with whatever he provides.

01:03:06.829 --> 01:03:08.829
And Paul certainly did that.

01:03:08.829 --> 01:03:10.829
He learned to trade to support himself,

01:03:10.829 --> 01:03:13.829
so as not to be a burden to others.

01:03:13.829 --> 01:03:15.829
He was fully occupied with his ministry,

01:03:15.829 --> 01:03:18.829
so he had few material possessions,

01:03:18.829 --> 01:03:21.829
but he was grateful for the brotherhood.

01:03:21.829 --> 01:03:25.829
He was appreciative of what those brothers were able to provide,

01:03:25.829 --> 01:03:27.829
what he needed.

01:03:27.829 --> 01:03:30.829
Paul learned through each of these experiences.

01:03:30.829 --> 01:03:34.829
And as he saw Jehovah's hand in his life,

01:03:34.829 --> 01:03:37.829
it became apparent to him that no matter what his circumstances were,

01:03:38.829 --> 01:03:43.829
he had to look to Jehovah to satisfy his needs.

01:03:43.829 --> 01:03:45.829
Did you notice verse 13,

01:03:45.829 --> 01:03:48.829
Jehovah sustained Paul.

01:03:48.829 --> 01:03:50.829
He gave him power.

01:03:50.829 --> 01:03:54.829
So when Paul did face those adverse circumstances,

01:03:54.829 --> 01:03:57.829
he was still able to be content,

01:03:57.829 --> 01:03:59.829
maintain inner joy,

01:03:59.829 --> 01:04:04.369
and carry out his ministry.

01:04:04.369 --> 01:04:08.369
Well, what can you and I learn from Paul's example?

01:04:08.369 --> 01:04:13.369
It may be that we too might face hunger for a variety of reasons.

01:04:13.369 --> 01:04:16.369
For example, food shortages.

01:04:16.369 --> 01:04:21.369
This could result from civil unrest or an economic crisis.

01:04:21.369 --> 01:04:25.369
World events today have caused many to lose their jobs around the world,

01:04:25.369 --> 01:04:27.369
including our brothers.

01:04:27.369 --> 01:04:34.369
So a personal economic setback may force us to live on less.

01:04:34.369 --> 01:04:37.369
Hunger can also result from persecution.

01:04:38.369 --> 01:04:41.369
When many of our brothers were put in Nazi concentration camps,

01:04:41.369 --> 01:04:46.369
depriving them of adequate food was one of the diabolical methods used

01:04:46.369 --> 01:04:50.369
in an effort to break their integrity.

01:04:50.369 --> 01:04:53.369
And even when it comes to theocratic pursuits,

01:04:53.369 --> 01:04:55.369
some who move to serve with the need is greater,

01:04:55.369 --> 01:04:58.369
are forced to make adjustments,

01:04:58.369 --> 01:05:02.369
and must learn to be content with less.

01:05:02.369 --> 01:05:05.369
So really, in any number of situations,

01:05:05.369 --> 01:05:11.369
you and I could experience a lack of food or even hunger.

01:05:11.369 --> 01:05:17.369
And that could make us feel anxious and distressed.

01:05:17.369 --> 01:05:24.369
But the antidote is trust and reliance on Jehovah.

01:05:24.369 --> 01:05:28.369
You know, when we do that, it helps us to remain calm

01:05:28.369 --> 01:05:33.369
and to take things one day at a time.

01:05:33.369 --> 01:05:37.369
When inflation hit in his country, one father said,

01:05:37.369 --> 01:05:42.369
my dearly prayer was simply that God would give us today our bread

01:05:42.369 --> 01:05:49.320
for this day in order for us to survive.

01:05:49.320 --> 01:05:54.320
We must also be grateful with whatever Jehovah provides.

01:05:54.320 --> 01:05:57.320
When that same father went to the food line to purchase items,

01:05:57.320 --> 01:06:00.320
he said, one time, the only thing they had left was

01:06:00.320 --> 01:06:03.320
something he didn't like.

01:06:03.320 --> 01:06:05.320
Oh, what did he do?

01:06:05.320 --> 01:06:11.320
He said, I didn't like it, but it was food.

01:06:11.320 --> 01:06:14.320
So that's what we ate that night.

01:06:14.320 --> 01:06:19.320
And he was grateful to Jehovah for providing it.

01:06:19.320 --> 01:06:22.320
You know, perhaps right now, we may be in a position

01:06:22.320 --> 01:06:25.320
where we only eat what we like.

01:06:25.320 --> 01:06:30.320
But if circumstances change, could we adjust

01:06:30.320 --> 01:06:33.320
and still be grateful?

01:06:33.320 --> 01:06:37.320
Isn't it reassuring that we are cared for by a God

01:06:37.320 --> 01:06:41.320
who gives us what we need?

01:06:41.320 --> 01:06:44.320
And of course, it is important that we utilize

01:06:44.320 --> 01:06:47.320
the resources Jehovah provides.

01:06:47.320 --> 01:06:50.320
We'd like you to watch the following video.

01:06:50.320 --> 01:06:53.320
As you do, note which provisions helped our sister

01:06:53.320 --> 01:07:14.219
to rejoice despite experiencing hunger.

01:07:14.219 --> 01:07:18.219
Well, here in Venezuela, long before the crisis,

01:07:18.219 --> 01:07:24.579
there weren't so many financial problems like we have today.

01:07:24.579 --> 01:07:28.579
We could go to the stores, we could buy the amount of food we wanted,

01:07:28.579 --> 01:07:37.110
and life was peaceful.

01:07:37.110 --> 01:07:43.900
For us, the situation started to get really bad five years ago.

01:07:43.900 --> 01:07:47.900
It was hard to get any food at all, even basic items.

01:07:47.900 --> 01:07:53.949
When it came time to buy something, well, it was all gone.

01:07:53.949 --> 01:07:57.949
There were two elders that I can say were checking on me almost daily,

01:07:57.949 --> 01:08:02.650
always asking how much food I needed.

01:08:02.650 --> 01:08:04.650
When I prepared it and served it,

01:08:04.650 --> 01:08:07.650
my main concern was that my children would get enough.

01:08:07.650 --> 01:08:13.619
I always gave them more food.

01:08:13.619 --> 01:08:18.470
Even though my youngest boy would ask,

01:08:18.470 --> 01:08:21.470
Mommy, is that what you're going to eat?

01:08:21.470 --> 01:08:25.470
I would tell him, yes, dear, I'm fine with this.

01:08:25.470 --> 01:08:28.470
Then he would say, I don't think so.

01:08:28.470 --> 01:08:35.340
I would think, I can handle this.

01:08:35.340 --> 01:08:38.340
But the amount that I was eating just wasn't enough for my body.

01:08:38.340 --> 01:08:48.939
One Sunday morning during the meeting, I wasn't feeling very well.

01:08:48.939 --> 01:08:51.939
But thanks to Jehovah, my daughter was nearby.

01:08:51.939 --> 01:08:56.939
When I came to, she said, Mom, you fainted three times.

01:08:56.939 --> 01:08:59.939
I said, that can't be.

01:08:59.939 --> 01:09:02.939
So the brothers immediately took me to the doctor.

01:09:02.939 --> 01:09:06.939
I was diagnosed as having severe malnutrition.

01:09:06.939 --> 01:09:12.659
The brothers began a plan of action.

01:09:12.659 --> 01:09:14.659
They brought food that was already prepared,

01:09:14.659 --> 01:09:20.029
and in fact, they would sit by me until I finished my food.

01:09:20.029 --> 01:09:23.029
I have not yet fully recovered my body weight,

01:09:23.029 --> 01:09:25.029
because I was a little heavier.

01:09:25.029 --> 01:09:28.029
But health wise, I have felt very well.

01:09:28.029 --> 01:09:34.039
The elders were always looking after me.

01:09:34.039 --> 01:09:38.039
That boosted my energy, and definitely, I never lost my joy.

01:09:38.039 --> 01:09:44.529
And it's all thanks to Jehovah.

01:09:44.529 --> 01:09:47.529
Thanks to him, because he is the one who sustains me.

01:09:47.529 --> 01:09:50.529
He cloaks me, he feeds me, and he gives me great friends.

01:09:50.529 --> 01:09:59.479
That is what Jehovah gives me.

01:09:59.479 --> 01:10:02.479
Did you notice the provisions that helped our sister?

01:10:02.479 --> 01:10:05.479
First, her relationship with Jehovah.

01:10:05.479 --> 01:10:08.479
She saw the importance of staying close to him

01:10:08.479 --> 01:10:11.479
and regularly attending her meetings.

01:10:11.479 --> 01:10:15.479
And then, of course, the Brotherhood.

01:10:15.479 --> 01:10:19.479
Wasn't it comforting to see how attentive the elders were?

01:10:19.479 --> 01:10:22.479
Making daily checks on her, providing food for her and her family,

01:10:22.479 --> 01:10:26.479
and even making sure she ate enough as well?

01:10:26.479 --> 01:10:29.479
Well, it's these same provisions,

01:10:29.479 --> 01:10:31.479
maintaining our relationship with Jehovah,

01:10:31.479 --> 01:10:34.479
receiving relief from the Brotherhood,

01:10:34.479 --> 01:10:38.479
as well as holding fast to our hope that can help us to rejoice,

01:10:38.479 --> 01:10:42.479
despite any periods of hunger.

01:10:42.479 --> 01:10:43.479
We agree.

01:10:43.479 --> 01:10:47.479
We are fully convinced of what Paul said in Philippians 412.

01:10:47.479 --> 01:10:55.479
Jehovah can and does provide life's necessities in all circumstances.

01:10:55.479 --> 01:11:01.920
When facing hunger, it is natural to be concerned for our own welfare

01:11:01.920 --> 01:11:03.920
and that of our loved ones.

01:11:03.920 --> 01:11:08.920
And yet, as we've seen, it is possible to rejoice.

01:11:08.920 --> 01:11:11.920
Despite any hunger, we may experience.

01:11:11.920 --> 01:11:16.920
But the key, learn the secret.

01:11:16.920 --> 01:11:18.920
Everyone likes to be in on a secret.

01:11:18.920 --> 01:11:23.920
And Jehovah is more than happy to reveal this one to us.

01:11:23.920 --> 01:11:30.920
But we must rely on him and see how he acts in our behalf.

01:11:30.920 --> 01:11:35.920
How pleased Jehovah must be when his servants remain loyal and joyful,

01:11:35.920 --> 01:11:39.920
trusting that he will never abandon them.

01:11:39.920 --> 01:11:45.390
For the Robert Lucioni, a helper to the publishing committee,

01:11:45.390 --> 01:11:49.390
will now present the next talk of this symposium.

01:11:49.390 --> 01:12:00.079
We can rejoice, despite nakedness.

01:12:00.079 --> 01:12:05.079
Is it possible to rejoice despite experiencing difficult trials?

01:12:05.079 --> 01:12:09.079
Thus far, we've seen how the Apostle Paul maintained his joy

01:12:09.079 --> 01:12:14.079
despite tribulation, distress, persecution, or even hunger.

01:12:14.079 --> 01:12:17.079
And note out, this has been encouragement to you

01:12:17.079 --> 01:12:22.079
because many of you have or are going through those very things.

01:12:22.079 --> 01:12:26.079
But what about situations where we lose everything,

01:12:26.079 --> 01:12:29.079
due to disasters or civil unrest?

01:12:29.079 --> 01:12:33.079
Can Paul's experience help us in that?

01:12:33.079 --> 01:12:36.079
Our theme scripture in Romans chapter 8, verse 35,

01:12:36.079 --> 01:12:41.079
quotes Paul stating that not even nakedness can separate us

01:12:41.079 --> 01:12:43.079
from the love of the Christ.

01:12:43.079 --> 01:12:46.079
And Paul had first-hand experience with that as well.

01:12:46.079 --> 01:12:51.079
It turned pleased to 2 Corinthians chapter 11 and verse 27

01:12:51.079 --> 01:12:54.079
and notice how he describes his trials.

01:12:54.079 --> 01:12:57.079
2 Corinthians 11, 27.

01:12:57.079 --> 01:13:03.079
In labor and toil, in sleepless nights often, in hunger and thirst,

01:13:03.079 --> 01:13:08.079
frequently without food, in cold and lacking clothing,

01:13:08.079 --> 01:13:11.079
or nakedness, as the footnote says.

01:13:11.079 --> 01:13:15.079
Now Paul's lack of clothing was not due to laziness on his part.

01:13:15.079 --> 01:13:20.079
We know from the scriptures that Paul worked hard to care for his needs.

01:13:20.079 --> 01:13:27.079
But rather, being cold and lacking clothing was due to things he experienced in his ministry.

01:13:27.079 --> 01:13:31.079
For example, remember the occasion when Paul was on board the ship

01:13:31.079 --> 01:13:36.079
that was driven and shipwrecked by that most violent wind on the Mediterranean

01:13:36.079 --> 01:13:42.079
as the ship broke to pieces, Paul and the others hung on to pieces of wood

01:13:42.079 --> 01:13:47.079
and pieces of the ship, and they may have reached land with little or no clothing on.

01:13:47.079 --> 01:13:53.079
In fact, remember the people of Malta had a build of fire to warm the cold survivors.

01:13:53.079 --> 01:13:58.079
On other occasions, Paul escaped for his life with just a close on his back.

01:13:58.079 --> 01:14:03.079
At other times, he was beaten or stoned, which surely ripped his clothes to shreds.

01:14:03.079 --> 01:14:08.079
And at Acts chapter 16, verse 22, we read in the account where the civil magistrates

01:14:09.079 --> 01:14:12.079
it says, after tearing their garments off of Paul,

01:14:12.079 --> 01:14:18.079
gave the command to beat him with rods and then threw him into prison.

01:14:18.079 --> 01:14:26.079
Well, these accounts help us to better understand Paul's words in 1 Corinthians chapter 4 and verse 11.

01:14:26.079 --> 01:14:31.079
1 Corinthians 4, 11, he says, down to this very hour,

01:14:31.079 --> 01:14:39.079
we continue to hunger and thirst and to be poorly clothed and to be beaten and to be homeless.

01:14:39.079 --> 01:14:45.079
But despite these circumstances, what did Paul encourage his fellow Christians to do?

01:14:45.079 --> 01:14:52.079
Look at verse 16. He says, I urge you, therefore, become imitators of me.

01:14:52.079 --> 01:14:57.079
See, he encouraged them to imitate his example, rejoice despite trials.

01:14:58.079 --> 01:15:03.079
In Romans chapter 12 and verse 12, we read where he tells us to rejoice in the hope,

01:15:03.079 --> 01:15:06.079
share what the holy ones according to their need.

01:15:06.079 --> 01:15:13.079
See, Paul was able to rejoice and help others even when experiencing great loss himself.

01:15:13.079 --> 01:15:18.079
Now, many of our dear brothers and sisters have been affected by terrible disasters.

01:15:18.079 --> 01:15:21.079
Just consider a few over the past year.

01:15:21.079 --> 01:15:29.079
Now, earthquakes in Albania, the Philippines, Puerto Rico and elsewhere, a severe flooding in Congo,

01:15:29.079 --> 01:15:39.079
Spain, the United States, hurricanes and typhoons in the Bahamas and the Philippines, terrible fires in Australia

01:15:39.079 --> 01:15:42.079
and the United States and the list goes on and on.

01:15:42.079 --> 01:15:47.079
And see the result of these and many other disasters is that our brothers and sisters,

01:15:47.079 --> 01:15:53.079
some of you have had to flee their homes in the middle of the night and we're just to close on their back

01:15:53.079 --> 01:15:58.079
or in other situations the disaster destroyed all of their belongings.

01:15:58.079 --> 01:16:02.079
It pains us when we hear those reports.

01:16:02.079 --> 01:16:09.079
And you dear brothers and sisters who are going through these things, please know that we keep you in our prayers.

01:16:09.079 --> 01:16:14.079
But even in those circumstances, our brothers continue to rejoice.

01:16:14.079 --> 01:16:17.079
How is that possible?

01:16:17.079 --> 01:16:28.079
Well, as you watch the following video, note which provisions helped our brother and sister to rejoice despite a period of inadequate clothing.

01:16:28.079 --> 01:16:43.779
Well, one thing you have to understand about living in New York City is that it's a very fast-paced life.

01:16:43.779 --> 01:16:47.779
So you got to keep up with that lifestyle.

01:16:48.779 --> 01:16:51.779
We were doing pretty fine and we were happy.

01:16:51.779 --> 01:16:56.779
Pine Aaron, working, just trying to survive in New York.

01:16:56.779 --> 01:17:00.779
Some of the things that you usually have to worry about is your safety.

01:17:00.779 --> 01:17:03.779
Being careful of your surroundings.

01:17:03.779 --> 01:17:09.779
But hurricanes is just something we never considered. It's something we never had to worry about.

01:17:09.779 --> 01:17:20.579
The day when we first heard the warnings, it was raining outside, kind of windy.

01:17:20.579 --> 01:17:24.579
We saw the water coming into the parking lot where our apartment was.

01:17:24.579 --> 01:17:32.640
And that's when I realized something was about to happen.

01:17:32.640 --> 01:17:36.640
We got out with the clothes on our back.

01:17:36.640 --> 01:17:39.640
We just total devastation.

01:17:39.640 --> 01:17:42.640
We lose everything.

01:17:42.640 --> 01:17:46.079
One thing a night.

01:17:46.079 --> 01:17:53.079
I never had any thought that the water would come into our place and destroy everything from our material possessions to our clothes.

01:17:53.079 --> 01:17:57.079
I truly felt what it was like to be destitute.

01:17:57.079 --> 01:18:03.079
It just broke my heart and all I could do was wonder where do me and my wife go from here.

01:18:03.079 --> 01:18:08.159
Our assembly was scheduled for that weekend.

01:18:08.159 --> 01:18:12.159
I didn't even have a suit jacket or a tie.

01:18:12.159 --> 01:18:19.439
I think I probably took for granted something simple as clothing. I always had it.

01:18:19.439 --> 01:18:24.439
But the brothers and sisters stepped into us in so many different ways.

01:18:24.439 --> 01:18:34.439
I would hear a knock on the door that Friday with three suits and shoes.

01:18:34.439 --> 01:18:36.439
They purchased clothing for us.

01:18:36.439 --> 01:18:42.439
It was a more unbelievable experience. These friends gave us big hugs, gave us envelopes.

01:18:42.439 --> 01:18:45.439
We are fully convinced we were clothed by Jehovah's love.

01:18:45.439 --> 01:18:53.439
We were able to go to our assembly and enjoy taking in spiritual food, even though we were in that situation.

01:18:53.439 --> 01:19:01.439
Even though we lost everything physically, we were still able to keep on pioneering which we have been doing up to this day.

01:19:01.439 --> 01:19:04.439
Jehovah made a promise.

01:19:04.439 --> 01:19:10.439
But once we keep seeking for his kingdom, everything else he would take care of.

01:19:10.439 --> 01:19:13.439
And that's where my joy comes from.

01:19:14.439 --> 01:19:20.439
No matter what type of tribulation you go through in your life, even if it's to the point of nakedness,

01:19:20.439 --> 01:19:27.439
it will never ever be able to stop or cut off the relationship that we have with our God, Jehovah.

01:19:27.439 --> 01:19:35.850
Did you notice what helped this couple?

01:19:35.850 --> 01:19:40.850
They lost everything in one night. They were unsure what they would do, how they would go on.

01:19:40.850 --> 01:19:42.850
But did you notice they resolved?

01:19:42.850 --> 01:19:52.850
Remember Brian said, no matter what tribulation we experience, even to the point of nakedness, it will never cut us off from our relationship with Jehovah.

01:19:52.850 --> 01:19:59.850
They were touched by how their brothers stepped in to help them. They kept their hope in Jehovah and the future alive.

01:19:59.850 --> 01:20:02.850
But what do we learn from this?

01:20:02.850 --> 01:20:10.850
Well, we learn that when we are going through trials, even those trials that cause us to lose our possessions or be inadequately clothed,

01:20:10.850 --> 01:20:16.850
we can maintain our joy due to the three things we've been discussing.

01:20:16.850 --> 01:20:25.850
Maintaining our relationship with Jehovah, receiving relief from our brotherhood and holding fast to our hope.

01:20:25.850 --> 01:20:33.850
Now, many of you immediately respond to help your brothers and sisters when you see a need and we appreciate that so much.

01:20:33.850 --> 01:20:43.850
A disaster is on the increase, both in frequency and intensity, and so thus the need to provide relief for our brothers continues to increase.

01:20:43.850 --> 01:20:51.850
And we commend you and thank you for what you do, why some of you volunteer to go into areas to help.

01:20:51.850 --> 01:21:02.850
For example, after Hurricane Dorian, in the Bahamas, witness pilots transported more than 700 volunteer workers into those affected areas.

01:21:02.850 --> 01:21:07.850
Others of you assist your brothers and sisters right in your own area.

01:21:07.850 --> 01:21:16.850
For example, in Congo, many of our brothers had to flee their homes and villages with just a clothes on their back due to civil unrest.

01:21:16.850 --> 01:21:20.850
With all their possessions and livelihood gone, what would they do?

01:21:20.850 --> 01:21:32.850
Well, their brothers and sisters in neighboring congregations, even though they had limited means, provided money, food, clothing, and even housing for their displaced brothers.

01:21:32.850 --> 01:21:39.850
In Bolivia and Venezuela, a congregation shared meals or local distribution of food.

01:21:39.850 --> 01:21:55.850
And look at how our brotherhood has stepped in during this COVID-19 pandemic, providing food supplies, relief supplies, emotional support, spiritual support, congregations, families helping one another out.

01:21:55.850 --> 01:22:05.850
And see, due to your self-sacrificing spirit and your generous donations, you are a blessing to your brothers and sisters all around the world.

01:22:06.850 --> 01:22:11.850
And what a slap in the face this is to Satan.

01:22:11.850 --> 01:22:13.850
Now, why do we say that?

01:22:13.850 --> 01:22:26.850
Well, you remember in Job chapter 1 and verse 11, Satan insulted Jehovah, and all of us who loved Jehovah by insinuating that we would turn our back on Jehovah when going through trials.

01:22:26.850 --> 01:22:30.850
Let's look at that. In Job chapter 1 and verse 11, he says,

01:22:30.850 --> 01:22:39.850
But before a change, stretch out your hand and strike everything he has, and he will surely curse you to your very face.

01:22:39.850 --> 01:22:47.850
See, Satan was convinced that when it came to losing our possessions or staying loyal to Jehovah, we would choose our possessions.

01:22:47.850 --> 01:22:54.850
Satan was convinced when it came to helping ourselves or helping somebody else, we would choose ourselves.

01:22:55.850 --> 01:23:03.850
How wrong he was. How angry he must be when he sees what is happening in Jehovah's organization today.

01:23:03.850 --> 01:23:05.850
So what do we need to do?

01:23:05.850 --> 01:23:07.850
Keep making him angry.

01:23:07.850 --> 01:23:10.850
Continue to help your brothers and sisters in need.

01:23:10.850 --> 01:23:17.850
And when we do not only do we gain happiness, but we help our brothers to rejoice as well.

01:23:18.850 --> 01:23:27.850
Dear friends, may all of us be determined to keep our joy alive by doing those three things, maintaining our relationship with Jehovah,

01:23:27.850 --> 01:23:34.850
