Keep assuring your heart of his love.

01:47:06.699 --> 01:47:11.699
Treasure our precious brotherhood and draw closer to one another.

01:47:11.699 --> 01:47:16.699
Cherish your God-given hope and meditate on the real life yet ahead.

01:47:16.699 --> 01:47:22.699
And finally, remember the inspired prayer found at Colossians 1-11.

01:47:22.699 --> 01:47:31.699
If we continue doing these things dear friends, then like Paul, we will be able to rejoice despite trials of any sort.

01:47:31.699 --> 01:47:38.699
Notice these encouraging words found at Colossians chapter 1 and verse 11.

01:47:38.699 --> 01:47:47.699
And may you be strengthened with all power according to his glorious might.

01:47:47.699 --> 01:47:52.699
Now, just how much power is there according to God's glorious might?

01:47:52.699 --> 01:47:59.699
We don't have to imagine because his word reveals what Jehovah has accomplished and will yet accomplished by means of his Holy Spirit.

01:47:59.699 --> 01:48:05.699
The most powerful force there is. And for what purpose will he grant you this?

01:48:05.699 --> 01:48:08.699
Not simply so that you may endure.

01:48:08.699 --> 01:48:11.699
Not merely so that you may endure fully.

01:48:11.699 --> 01:48:16.699
Not only so that you may endure fully with patience.

01:48:16.699 --> 01:48:23.699
But as it says, so that you may endure fully with patience and joy.

01:48:24.699 --> 01:48:31.699
And with that assurance, we can endure despite any trial, no matter how difficult it is, no matter how long it lasts,

01:48:31.699 --> 01:48:42.420
because our Father's unfailing love will enable us to rejoice, both for all eternity and always.

01:48:42.420 --> 01:48:45.420
Thank you brothers for those strengthening talks.

01:48:45.420 --> 01:48:52.420
And we thank Jehovah that he provides what we need to safeguard our joy.

01:48:52.420 --> 01:48:56.420
Let us now stand and sing together song number 9.

01:48:56.420 --> 01:48:58.420
Jehovah is our King.

01:48:58.420 --> 01:49:01.420
Again, that is song number 9.
